<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="706" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.01/40: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-18T11:00:00-04:00">August 18, 1937—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>25. Department’s 12, August 17, 6 p.m. Meeting not in a body, diplomats
                            called at various times between 4:30 and 6 o’clock. Failing instructions
                            I did not call. Minister for Foreign Affairs stated that the government
                            is returning to the constitution of 1870 and that international
                            obligations will be respected.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>